Residents cannot get services at the Laikipia government offices because officers are busy campaigning, the county assembly has been told.&ldquo;We ask (Governor Joshua) Irungu and his chief of staff John Wambugu to control the officers because people are suffering a lot,&rdquo; Igwamiti MCA Joseph Kabaci (pictured) said on Thursday.The House was debating a motion on bursaries, which have been delayed by the county government.